description:
When Ezekiel prophesied against the heathen ruler Gog, in Ezekiel 38-39, his words had both a literal and a symbolic meaning. Explore the end-time significance of Gog and Magog in this study of Scriptures prophecies. Francois DuPlessis explains this prophecy from a historical perspective and, then, explains that there is a spiritual war that will occur between the spiritual Magog and spiritual Israel. Listen to Francois DuPlessis address this end time war in which he explains who is the real "Gog" of the end times.
